 *    - If $rootU = rootV = R$, we have $P(u, R) = d[u]$ and $P(v, R) = d[v]$.
 *    - The existing path $P(u, v) = P(u, R) \oplus P(R, v) = d[u] \oplus d[v]$.
 *    - The new cycle sum is $P(u, v) \oplus w = (d[u] \oplus d[v]) \oplus w$.
