    // We need to maintain the property that every cycle has an even total weight.
    // This property is equivalent to saying that for any two nodes u and v,
    // the parity of the path weight between them is unique, regardless of the path chosen,
    // as long as the graph is connected.
    // If a cycle has an odd weight, say w(C) = 1 (mod 2), then adding this cycle
    // allows for two paths between any two nodes on the cycle with different path weight parities.
    //
